					</ul>
</div>

<p style="color: #000000; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Tool Design &amp; Construction</span></p>
<p style="color: #000000; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Engineering of tool is a key element of the success of Molded Dimensions. Our personnel profile, their individual and collective knowledge and experience is put into every product we produce for our customers.</span></p>
<p style="color: #000000; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">The result is the right product, on time, at the right price for our customers. Our in house tool design abilities guarantee a better tool design. Proper tool design is the key to ensuring a better quality part and an optimal manufacturing process. These are both important for long term success. We support long term relationships with local tool vendors to construct both rapid prototype molds and production molds as well as for regularly scheduled mold maintenance. Our Engineering staff is both capable and skilled in CAD/CAM, Solid, ProE software.</span></p>


</div>

